      "content": "---\nstepsCompleted: [1]\ninputDocuments: []\nsession_topic: 'PR validation pipeline for AVD Image Factory Terraform infrastructure'\nsession_goals: 'Discover risks, gaps, blind spots, and edge cases before implementation'\nselected_approach: ''\ntechniques_used: []\nideas_generated: []\ncontext_file: ''\n---\n\n# Brainstorming Session Results\n\n**Facilitator:** Barbosa\n**Date:** 2026-03-13\n\n## Session Overview\n\n**Topic:** PR validation pipeline for AVD Image Factory Terraform infrastructure\n**Goals:** Discover risks, gaps, blind spots, and edge cases before implementation\n\n### Context Guidance\n\n_Project uses Terraform >= 1.9 with AzureRM 4.25.0, pre-commit hooks (terraform_fmt, terraform_validate, terraform_docs, terrascan, trivy, tfsec, snyk-iac), Makefile-based operations, dual codebase (root legacy + dev/terraform active), Packer-built Ubuntu 22.04 images, Azure Bastion access, Spot VMs, NAT Gateway, HIPAA compliance tags._\n\n### Session Setup\n\n_Brainstorming focused on surfacing risks and edge cases in designing a PR validation pipeline for this infrastructure-as-code project. The existing pre-commit hooks provide local validation but there is no CI/CD pipeline for PR-level validation yet._\n"
